> Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act (5 ILCS 140), I
> respectfully request the following records related to the collection of
> fines assessed through Administrative Notice of Violations (ANOVs) issued
> by Chicago Police Department Transit Section officers for transit-related
> violations on Chicago Transit Authority property.
>
> Background: I contacted the Department of Administrative Hearings (DOAH)
> regarding collection records for transit ANOVs. DOAH's FOIA liaison
> confirmed explicitly that DOAH does not collect fines and therefore has n=
o
> collection records. DOAH indicated that the Department of Finance may be
> the appropriate custodian of this data. This request is filed on that bas=
is.
>
> Record Set Requested:
>
> For each calendar year 2018 through present, records sufficient to show:
>
> 1. Total fines levied on ANOVs issued for transit-related violations on
> CTA property, broken out by year and by violation code or violation
> category if available in aggregate if not.
>
> 2. Total fines collected on those ANOVs, broken out by year.
>
> 3. Total outstanding balances on transit-related ANOVs written off,
> discharged, or referred to a third-party collections agency, broken out b=
y
> year.
>
> 4. The collection rate (fines collected as a percentage of fines levied)
> for transit-related ANOVs, by year, if tracked as a derived metric.
>
> 5. If the Department of Finance does not maintain transit-specific
> breakdowns, records sufficient to show total administrative adjudication
> fine revenue collected citywide by year, along with any documentation
> identifying which issuing department or violation category the revenue is
> attributed to.
>
> If the Department of Finance does not maintain any of these records,
> please provide written notice to that effect pursuant to 5 ILCS 140/8(g),
> and identify in writing the city department or office that does.
>
> I am willing to accept records in electronic format. If any portion of
> this request is denied, please cite the specific statutory exemption
> authorizing each denial pursuant to 5 ILCS 140/9(a).
>
> Thank you for your attention to this request.
>
> Michael Russo
